01:07:03.990 --> 01:07:05.520
the can down the road, right?

01:07:05.520 --> 01:07:10.110
So you need a much
greater kind of effort.

01:07:10.110 --> 01:07:12.930
And of course, in China we know
that the principle problem has

01:07:12.930 --> 01:07:16.240
to do with the mixed messages.

01:07:16.240 --> 01:07:19.980
So the center grandpa is
always says good things,

01:07:19.980 --> 01:07:22.090
and even abolishes your taxes.

01:07:22.090 --> 01:07:25.660
But then the local government
has to then pick up the flag,

01:07:25.660 --> 01:07:26.370
right?

01:07:26.370 --> 01:07:28.620
Or pick up whatever
you have to pick up,

01:07:28.620 --> 01:07:30.690
and they have profit
motives, right?

01:07:30.690 --> 01:07:32.740
They have production
targets and so on.

01:07:32.740 --> 01:07:34.320
So that's always
a kind of tension.

01:07:34.320 --> 01:07:37.650
So but nonetheless,
environmental NGOs

01:07:37.650 --> 01:07:41.070
have grown by leaps
and bounds in China.

01:07:41.070 --> 01:07:42.690
They have become--

01:07:42.690 --> 01:07:46.840
I don't know if I have it here.

01:07:46.840 --> 01:07:48.740
I'll just come back to that.

01:07:48.740 --> 01:07:49.830
I have to show you that.

01:07:53.200 --> 01:08:00.480
Yeah, the numbers in 2008, there
were 2,768 environmental NGOs.

01:08:00.480 --> 01:08:03.780
And by 2013, this
had gone up to 8,000.

01:08:03.780 --> 01:08:05.520
This is one area
of civil society,

01:08:05.520 --> 01:08:07.800
the green public sphere,
which is permitted

01:08:07.800 --> 01:08:09.840
in China to some extent.

01:08:09.840 --> 01:08:12.570
And the reason it is
permitted is because in a way

01:08:12.570 --> 01:08:14.430
they act as watchdogs.

01:08:14.430 --> 01:08:18.810
They're not activists so much
as protectionists, right?

01:08:18.810 --> 01:08:19.590
They're watchdogs.

01:08:19.590 --> 01:08:22.740
Because the laws are all on
the books, the laws are there,

01:08:22.740 --> 01:08:25.470
but it's really
the implementation.

01:08:25.470 --> 01:08:27.479
So between the media and these--

01:08:27.479 --> 01:08:29.729
and the NGOs you begin to get--

01:08:29.729 --> 01:08:31.830
five minutes more.

01:08:31.830 --> 01:08:40.260
You'll begin to get some kind
of legal results as well.

01:08:40.260 --> 01:08:43.740
But it's a mixed story, of
course, as you'd expect.

01:08:43.740 --> 01:08:46.810
I'll just go back
to this Daoism.

01:08:46.810 --> 01:08:50.850
Now talking about pertinence
and Daoism let me just--

01:08:53.779 --> 01:08:56.060
this is Dao-- you
know the Dao is

01:08:56.060 --> 01:09:01.520
in China, in the post
[INAUDIBLE],, the post opening

01:09:01.520 --> 01:09:05.420
years, have been much less
successful in getting attention

01:09:05.420 --> 01:09:08.149
than the Buddhists or
the Confucianists, right?

01:09:08.149 --> 01:09:11.550
And there's no sort of natural
global constituency for them.

01:09:11.550 --> 01:09:13.250
Naturally is important.

01:09:13.250 --> 01:09:17.997
And so when this alliance of
religions and conservations

01:09:17.997 --> 01:09:19.580
approached them--
this is, by the way,

01:09:19.580 --> 01:09:22.899
this is an alliance that's
based in Bath, in England.

01:09:22.899 --> 01:09:25.529
It's been very, very big.

01:09:25.529 --> 01:09:29.270
And it really begins to try and
link up traditional religions

01:09:29.270 --> 01:09:32.420
with conservation efforts.

01:09:32.420 --> 01:09:35.670
They agreed to join
with them, and they

01:09:35.670 --> 01:09:43.460
became-- they declared Lowndes
to be the [INAUDIBLE],, right?

01:09:43.460 --> 01:09:46.010
So Lowndes has become
the protector god

01:09:46.010 --> 01:09:48.040
of the environment, right?

01:09:48.040 --> 01:09:49.040
This is what has become.

01:09:49.040 --> 01:09:51.529
He's officially stated as that.

01:09:51.529 --> 01:09:53.720
And when you go-- and
they, although they

01:09:53.720 --> 01:09:55.970
don't have huge
popular followings,

01:09:55.970 --> 01:09:57.940
they control all
the Daoist temples.

01:09:57.940 --> 01:10:00.680
And I just went to
Mao Shan last summer,

01:10:00.680 --> 01:10:04.370
and they control the temples.

01:10:04.370 --> 01:10:07.250
And they are
beautifully kept now.

01:10:07.250 --> 01:10:11.090
You're not allowed to burn more
than three sticks of incense.

01:10:11.090 --> 01:10:12.170
You have to recycle.

01:10:12.170 --> 01:10:15.530
You have to use
these, what you call,

01:10:15.530 --> 01:10:18.130
these photo roll take--
these, what are they called?

01:10:18.130 --> 01:10:21.300
Anyway, solar energy
and things like that.

01:10:21.300 --> 01:10:24.380
And they have strict rules
of all of these things.

01:10:24.380 --> 01:10:25.970
So at some level, it's working.

01:10:25.970 --> 01:10:28.670
And it is having a
kind of an impact.

01:10:28.670 --> 01:10:31.190
It's part of the
public sphere here.

01:10:31.190 --> 01:10:33.800
And here is-- I love this
flag of theirs, which

01:10:33.800 --> 01:10:36.590
is yin-yang in green, right?

01:10:36.590 --> 01:10:37.605
The greening of Daoism.

01:10:40.700 --> 01:10:42.200
And then people
have found all kinds

01:10:42.200 --> 01:10:44.690
of things that have survived
the Chinese revolution

01:10:44.690 --> 01:10:48.410
and the Cultural Revolution,
like this fengshui forest.

01:10:48.410 --> 01:10:51.100
All over, there's
huge forest coverage.

01:10:51.100 --> 01:10:53.910
And fengshui, people are just
beginning to get into it.

01:10:53.910 --> 01:10:56.750
Because fengshui is just seen
as some kind of urban modern,

01:10:56.750 --> 01:10:59.960
urban fad, right?

01:10:59.960 --> 01:11:03.920
But in fact, it's the
[INAUDIBLE] very much

01:11:03.920 --> 01:11:08.660
at the core of it is this idea
of the organic nature of human

01:11:08.660 --> 01:11:12.720
and natural prosperity, that
the two cannot be separated.

01:11:12.720 --> 01:11:16.250
So you have Chris Coggins is
doing very good work on this

01:11:16.250 --> 01:11:18.700
with his whole team in China.

01:11:18.700 --> 01:11:20.750
And the Chinese
local government,

01:11:20.750 --> 01:11:23.000
several local governments
have become involved in this

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:24.230
as well.

01:11:24.230 --> 01:11:26.210
There's one thing
that more I want

01:11:26.210 --> 01:11:28.454
to talk about the Chinese
green public sphere,

01:11:28.454 --> 01:11:29.870
on the global green
public sphere,

01:11:29.870 --> 01:11:33.560
and the relationship
between these popular--

01:11:33.560 --> 01:11:36.560
and whether or not
religious movements

01:11:36.560 --> 01:11:38.320
and global civil society.

01:11:38.320 --> 01:11:40.440
I'll give you just one example.

01:11:40.440 --> 01:11:45.710
In the mid 1990s,
in the early 1990s

01:11:45.710 --> 01:11:48.500
when the Three Gorges
Dam was being set up,

01:11:48.500 --> 01:11:49.340
was being planned.

01:11:49.340 --> 01:11:52.040
And the construction had begun,
the surveying had taken place,

01:11:52.040 --> 01:11:53.690
and so on.

01:11:53.690 --> 01:11:56.660
And the Chinese
government had gotten

01:11:56.660 --> 01:12:00.020
billions of dollars
of funding from not

01:12:00.020 --> 01:12:03.650
just the Western governments,
not just IMF and World Bank,

01:12:03.650 --> 01:12:06.020
but also Morgan Stanley
and other investment banks

01:12:06.020 --> 01:12:07.830
and so on.

01:12:07.830 --> 01:12:10.400
And there were of course
moments of protests

01:12:10.400 --> 01:12:13.580
from local scientists and so
on, but nothing was-- no fuss

01:12:13.580 --> 01:12:17.330
was made until Dai Qing
wrote the book [INAUDIBLE],,

01:12:17.330 --> 01:12:20.000
which got translated
immediately.

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:23.720
And by 1999, when the
Chinese government

01:12:23.720 --> 01:12:27.740
went for the second tranche
of its billions of dollars,

01:12:27.740 --> 01:12:30.470
none of these
governments, not the IMF,

01:12:30.470 --> 01:12:34.130
not the World Bank,
not even Morgan Stanley

01:12:34.130 --> 01:12:38.660
gave it the money because
it had been lobbied

01:12:38.660 --> 01:12:41.380
by environmental groups.

01:12:41.380 --> 01:12:43.850
Its shareholders had been
lobbied, right, and told

01:12:43.850 --> 01:12:45.780
to avoid this kind of thing.

01:12:45.780 --> 01:12:50.660
So I mean, you can see
how a small little stir

01:12:50.660 --> 01:12:54.770
can make a huge global
scale sort of activism.

01:12:54.770 --> 01:12:57.920
So it became much more expensive
for the Chinese government.

01:12:57.920 --> 01:13:00.170
And it's still a
very dicey project.

01:13:00.170 --> 01:13:04.010
They claim that the 2008
earthquake, as you've heard,

01:13:04.010 --> 01:13:06.350
was a consequence of the
settling of the reservoir,

01:13:06.350 --> 01:13:07.740
the final reservoir.

01:13:07.740 --> 01:13:10.700
And apparently [INAUDIBLE]
