Yangtze Valley and so on.

01:13:20.060 --> 01:13:21.980
Apparently that didn't happen.

01:13:21.980 --> 01:13:24.150
But this is happening all over.

01:13:24.150 --> 01:13:26.930
Suddenly, all over Southeast
Asia and the Mekong Delta,

01:13:26.930 --> 01:13:29.790
you know about Myitsone, the
Burmese [INAUDIBLE] thing

01:13:29.790 --> 01:13:34.130
that canceled-- was
canceled in 2011 and so on.

01:13:34.130 --> 01:13:36.170
And Yunnan of course
is the great cradle

01:13:36.170 --> 01:13:37.430
of all of these movements.

01:13:37.430 --> 01:13:39.740
And that Yunnan southeast
Asian connection

01:13:39.740 --> 01:13:44.240
is very interesting as a
transnational area of activism.

01:13:44.240 --> 01:13:48.731
So my final, I hope--

01:13:48.731 --> 01:13:49.230
yeah.

01:13:52.880 --> 01:13:54.830
So I think that's--

01:13:54.830 --> 01:13:57.860
so you have these two
different notions of sacrality

01:13:57.860 --> 01:14:00.410
that are beginning to sort
of come together in Yunnan

01:14:00.410 --> 01:14:02.330
in an unstable kind of way.

01:14:02.330 --> 01:14:06.080
One is the sort of religious
and-- well, actually two.

01:14:06.080 --> 01:14:08.570
One is the religious, the
other is local communities,

01:14:08.570 --> 01:14:11.990
marginal communities who have
a certain conception of nature

01:14:11.990 --> 01:14:13.010
around them.

01:14:13.010 --> 01:14:14.780
But the other is
the modern sector

01:14:14.780 --> 01:14:18.740
of civil society and
civic activism, which also

01:14:18.740 --> 01:14:20.600
includes a lot of scientists.

01:14:20.600 --> 01:14:25.550
And this is happening to the
idea of modern protection.

01:14:25.550 --> 01:14:28.020
And the best example
of this, of course,

01:14:28.020 --> 01:14:33.570
is the United Nations, a
common heritage of humankind.

01:14:33.570 --> 01:14:34.910
The protected regions, right?

01:14:34.910 --> 01:14:37.880
Legally, there are
160,000 legally

01:14:37.880 --> 01:14:41.370
protected areas in the world,
nationally and internationally,

01:14:41.370 --> 01:14:44.780
including about 1,000
World Heritage sites which

01:14:44.780 --> 01:14:46.130
are both cultural and natural.

01:14:46.130 --> 01:14:48.500
More of them are
about biodiversity.

01:14:48.500 --> 01:14:50.720
And it covers 12% of the
land area of the world.

01:14:50.720 --> 01:14:52.670
By the way, this doesn't
include the oceans,

01:14:52.670 --> 01:14:54.920
where most of the strangling--
a lot of the strangling

01:14:54.920 --> 01:14:56.364
is taking place.

01:14:56.364 --> 01:14:58.030
And some studies have
shown that they've

01:14:58.030 --> 01:15:00.470
reduced rates of deforestation,
protected species,

01:15:00.470 --> 01:15:02.670
and conserved land and water.

01:15:02.670 --> 01:15:05.900
I like to call this a kind
of a modern sacrality.

01:15:05.900 --> 01:15:07.700
Because after all,
what is involved here?

01:15:07.700 --> 01:15:09.470
It's an inviolability, right?

01:15:09.470 --> 01:15:12.260
When you protect an area,
you're saying it's inviolable.

01:15:12.260 --> 01:15:14.060
And why is it inviolable?

01:15:14.060 --> 01:15:16.940
Because it arises from
the elemental earth

01:15:16.940 --> 01:15:19.250
to protect the
sources of life, which

01:15:19.250 --> 01:15:23.750
is after all what also religious
sacrality is often related to.

01:15:23.750 --> 01:15:25.610
So there, at least
partially the legacy

01:15:25.610 --> 01:15:29.690
of ecological spirituality
and ecological activism.

01:15:29.690 --> 01:15:31.700
National and global
legal institutions

01:15:31.700 --> 01:15:33.910
are beginning to
recognize these demands.

01:15:33.910 --> 01:15:36.620
And we have examples
of the Indian Supreme

01:15:36.620 --> 01:15:40.730
Court, who declared that
the Orissa Kondh where

01:15:40.730 --> 01:15:43.970
in fact the most bauxite mining
in the world takes place,

01:15:43.970 --> 01:15:46.610
is declared the sacred
site of the Kondh.

01:15:46.610 --> 01:15:48.890
And so no more mining
can happen there.

01:15:48.890 --> 01:15:50.790
This has, of course,
other types of problems.

01:15:50.790 --> 01:15:53.460
But it's a very
interesting development.

01:15:53.460 --> 01:15:56.450
And there was a rash of
other legal protections then

01:15:56.450 --> 01:15:58.580
