01:19:35.450 --> 01:19:38.720
But people say, well, what
about the economic improvement

01:19:38.720 --> 01:19:42.230
of the people that are
benefiting by whatever

01:19:42.230 --> 01:19:44.690
this development is?

01:19:44.690 --> 01:19:47.720
So how do you tie the
two things together,

01:19:47.720 --> 01:19:53.840
the environmental protection
versus the movement

01:19:53.840 --> 01:19:56.980
forward to people to bettering
their economic standing?

01:20:00.042 --> 01:20:01.740
Should I answer
now, or take it--

01:20:01.740 --> 01:20:02.620
Oh sure, absolutely.

01:20:02.620 --> 01:20:08.020
Well, I did try to address
it in Tim Jackson's view,

01:20:08.020 --> 01:20:09.970
but of course that's
not an immediate view.

01:20:09.970 --> 01:20:11.440
That's the long term view.

01:20:11.440 --> 01:20:19.550
And I don't have a
program for action here.

01:20:19.550 --> 01:20:22.930
I do have a scholarly
view that in the agenda

01:20:22.930 --> 01:20:25.580
of environmental
humanities, what I argue

01:20:25.580 --> 01:20:29.150
is that we should still
be looking into issues.

01:20:29.150 --> 01:20:31.190
The traditional
pillars and categories

01:20:31.190 --> 01:20:38.630
of environmental studies
is adaptation, mitigation,

01:20:38.630 --> 01:20:42.020
political ecology, and
so on, to show who gains

01:20:42.020 --> 01:20:45.320
and who benefits by certain
environmental moves,

01:20:45.320 --> 01:20:48.560
and how the poor are often
left out of that, right?

01:20:48.560 --> 01:20:51.320
So to some extent,
you can address it

01:20:51.320 --> 01:20:57.170
through an ecologically
informed economic study,

01:20:57.170 --> 01:21:00.290
right, to address the
questions of poverty.

01:21:00.290 --> 01:21:03.620
Of course, there
are policy people

01:21:03.620 --> 01:21:06.870
who say that you can just do
what the Chinese are doing.

01:21:06.870 --> 01:21:09.140
The positive side of what
the Chinese are doing,

01:21:09.140 --> 01:21:13.040
is just build a lot of renewable
energy structures and so

01:21:13.040 --> 01:21:16.460
on that will generate
employment and so on too.

01:21:16.460 --> 01:21:20.240
But ultimately, I think we
have to move to the Tim Jackson

01:21:20.240 --> 01:21:24.380
argument, which is that we
have to get rid of the idea

01:21:24.380 --> 01:21:31.430
that wealth and economics
is related only to greater

01:21:31.430 --> 01:21:33.100
and greater production.

01:21:33.100 --> 01:21:35.960
That there has to be a
diversity of goals and values

01:21:35.960 --> 01:21:40.340
of what we think of as
prosperity, including

01:21:40.340 --> 01:21:44.090
the ways you use your time,
the kinds of activities

01:21:44.090 --> 01:21:45.660
you do with that, and so on.

01:21:45.660 --> 01:21:49.280
So I have a
three-pronged answer.

01:21:49.280 --> 01:21:51.650
I don't know if
it's satisfactory.

01:21:51.650 --> 01:21:54.060
Yeah, I think Bill
had a question.

01:21:54.060 --> 01:21:54.930
Yeah, over here.

01:21:54.930 --> 01:21:57.782
[INAUDIBLE] thank you
for a wonderful talk,

01:21:57.782 --> 01:21:59.620
and for a wonderful book.

01:21:59.620 --> 01:22:00.120
Thank you.

01:22:03.460 --> 01:22:09.530
And it's just wonderful to
have even an iota of optimism

01:22:09.530 --> 01:22:11.437
in the world on these issues.

01:22:11.437 --> 01:22:12.270
On almost any issue.

01:22:12.270 --> 01:22:15.390
[INAUDIBLE] from off the cuff.

01:22:15.390 --> 01:22:16.920
On the China front,
I guess I want

01:22:16.920 --> 01:22:18.420
to press you just
a little bit more,

01:22:18.420 --> 01:22:22.440
because I think Taiwan
is an example of what

01:22:22.440 --> 01:22:24.600
can happen obviously in
a Chinese cultural area.

01:22:24.600 --> 01:22:26.850
There are a variety
and extraordinary--

01:22:26.850 --> 01:22:29.820
Tsuji and other
organizations have

01:22:29.820 --> 01:22:31.080
been extraordinarily helpful.

01:22:31.080 --> 01:22:34.470
Having an opposition party
that is a Green Party also

01:22:34.470 --> 01:22:35.900
has something to do with it.

01:22:35.900 --> 01:22:36.526
But it in our--

01:22:36.526 --> 01:22:37.400
Of course, of course.

01:22:37.400 --> 01:22:39.840
-- own lifetime, since the
time when you and I as graduate

01:22:39.840 --> 01:22:41.840
students were in Taiwan,
we've seen the physical

01:22:41.840 --> 01:22:43.290
transformation of
this landscape.

01:22:43.290 --> 01:22:44.100
Absolutely.

01:22:44.100 --> 01:22:47.070
On the mainland by contrast,
you have obviously things

01:22:47.070 --> 01:22:48.690
in a quite different way.

01:22:48.690 --> 01:22:51.390
But the area, if I
were to think of where

01:22:51.390 --> 01:22:53.940
I would be optimistic of
where that would head,

01:22:53.940 --> 01:22:57.450
it's actually sadly not
because of civil society,

01:22:57.450 --> 01:23:03.780
or because of local activists
in Yunnan, or whatever.

01:23:03.780 --> 01:23:08.580
It would be because of a kind of
relentless engineering on top,

01:23:08.580 --> 01:23:11.740
or the guy who really turned
the Ministry of Engineering,

01:23:11.740 --> 01:23:14.170
I'm sorry, of environmental
protection around.

01:23:14.170 --> 01:23:17.310
[INAUDIBLE],, former
president of [INAUDIBLE]..

01:23:17.310 --> 01:23:20.400
You now have a
relentless crackdown

01:23:20.400 --> 01:23:23.420
on coal-fired
power plants and so

01:23:23.420 --> 01:23:27.000
on all across the country
in terms of production.

01:23:27.000 --> 01:23:29.030
One size fits all.

01:23:29.030 --> 01:23:31.380
And my guess is that
this is going to,

01:23:31.380 --> 01:23:33.090
to the degree that
this happens, will

01:23:33.090 --> 01:23:37.080
make a dent and a difference
faster almost than anything

01:23:37.080 --> 01:23:37.830
else.

01:23:37.830 --> 01:23:41.430
But the civil
society part, which

01:23:41.430 --> 01:23:44.430
is the truly optimistic one
if this is a global movement,

01:23:44.430 --> 01:23:49.860
how do you see this in a
world governed by Xi Jinping

01:23:49.860 --> 01:23:52.200
Souchong?

01:23:52.200 --> 01:23:55.560
And in a world in which civil
society, and particularly

01:23:55.560 --> 01:23:58.860
religious affiliated
civil society,

01:23:58.860 --> 01:24:00.120
is under such pressure.

01:24:00.120 --> 01:24:03.120
Last thing I'll say, I
remember when he came to power.

01:24:03.120 --> 01:24:06.412
A friend of mine, a Buddhist,
said to me, don't worry.

01:24:06.412 --> 01:24:07.620
Don't worry about Xi Jinping.

01:24:07.620 --> 01:24:09.980
He's secretly a Buddhist.

01:24:09.980 --> 01:24:11.646
He's going to bring
the Dalai Lama back.

01:24:11.646 --> 01:24:12.340
[INAUDIBLE]

01:24:12.340 --> 01:24:17.500
So give me some
hope on that front.

01:24:17.500 --> 01:24:21.360
Well, I think that we
are not yet in a position

01:24:21.360 --> 01:24:23.700
to say that civil
society will develop,

01:24:23.700 --> 01:24:25.440
will flourish in
China or something,

01:24:25.440 --> 01:24:27.600
but I think it does play a role.

01:24:27.600 --> 01:24:29.970
And while there is
a huge crackdown

01:24:29.970 --> 01:24:33.490
as well under Jinping, I'm not
sure it is happening so much

01:24:33.490 --> 01:24:34.740
in the environment over there.

01:24:34.740 --> 01:24:37.990
I haven't followed the
contemporary scene that much.

01:24:37.990 --> 01:24:40.440
But certainly there
are still all kinds

01:24:40.440 --> 01:24:42.420
of protests that are going on.

01:24:42.420 --> 01:24:45.960
I mean, not environmentally
related, but land related.

01:24:45.960 --> 01:24:50.340
And I think that is an
important dimension of it,

01:24:50.340 --> 01:24:52.740
because when you control
the land, I mean,

01:24:52.740 --> 01:24:54.420
you can sell it
off or something.

01:24:54.420 --> 01:24:57.330
But right now, with
the property situation,

01:24:57.330 --> 01:25:01.410
people still have, in most parts
of China, a share to the land.

01:25:01.410 --> 01:25:05.860
And they're recognizing that
they cannot let that go easily,

01:25:05.860 --> 01:25:06.360
right?

01:25:06.360 --> 01:25:07.901
In some parts of
South China, they're

01:25:07.901 --> 01:25:10.710
being transformed into
cities and so on or whatever,

01:25:10.710 --> 01:25:14.200
semi-urban residential things.

01:25:14.200 --> 01:25:18.750
But I think there are forces
in society, not civil society

01:25:18.750 --> 01:25:23.220
forces, but forces in society
that have not angled it

01:25:23.220 --> 01:25:25.650
necessarily in an
environmental direction

01:25:25.650 --> 01:25:27.360
but in a land
direction, which I think

01:25:27.360 --> 01:25:28.930
is an important component.

01:25:28.930 --> 01:25:30.660
So that's the very
long and slow,

01:25:30.660 --> 01:25:31.990
but you're absolutely right.

01:25:31.990 --> 01:25:33.720
This is the biggest challenge.

01:25:33.720 --> 01:25:39.690
And I do think-- and Jinping
is working on the gamble,

01:25:39.690 --> 01:25:43.140
on the bet, the wager
that just having

01:25:43.140 --> 01:25:47.310
a lot of renewable energy
will do a lot of good stuff.

01:25:47.310 --> 01:25:50.280
And a lot of engineering
technical stuff

01:25:50.280 --> 01:25:53.220
that they're doing as well,
and with rivers and so

01:25:53.220 --> 01:25:57.580
on, though I think that is
going to be another disaster.

01:25:57.580 --> 01:25:59.620
These are these big projects.

01:25:59.620 --> 01:26:04.860
So I think it really is
also rural urban becoming

01:26:04.860 --> 01:26:07.290
increasingly-- not only
east coastal thing,

01:26:07.290 --> 01:26:11.400
but a rural urban thing where
you can see contamination where

01:26:11.400 --> 01:26:13.560
you cannot, right?

01:26:13.560 --> 01:26:14.920
This is a global problem.

01:26:14.920 --> 01:26:18.600
But it's even bigger in China,
because it's that much more

01:26:18.600 --> 01:26:21.645
difficult to see
in those places.

01:26:21.645 --> 01:26:23.520
But I don't have a good
answer, you're right.

01:26:23.520 --> 01:26:28.080
That is a global
weakness at this point.

01:26:28.080 --> 01:26:30.120
Though I'd be interested
in other views,

01:26:30.120 --> 01:26:33.630
if people are more optimistic
about Xi's top-down approach.

01:26:36.450 --> 01:26:37.570
I have a question here.

01:26:37.570 --> 01:26:38.790
I have a number of questions.

01:26:38.790 --> 01:26:40.579
And we'll move--
we'll move through.

01:26:40.579 --> 01:26:41.620
That's fine, that's fine.

01:26:41.620 --> 01:26:43.980
Robin will be next on the--

01:26:43.980 --> 01:26:44.480
OK.

01:26:44.480 --> 01:26:46.240
[INAUDIBLE]

01:26:46.240 --> 01:26:48.410
The mic, the baton.

01:26:48.410 --> 01:26:50.170
So, I'm disheartened,
as someone who

01:26:50.170 --> 01:26:53.380
spent half his professional
life in energy efficiency,

01:26:53.380 --> 01:26:56.230
and the other half
in renewable energy.

01:26:56.230 --> 01:26:57.130
And have a deep--

01:26:57.130 --> 01:26:58.570
I'm sorry, you are, sir?

01:26:58.570 --> 01:27:00.060
I'm George Wood.

01:27:00.060 --> 01:27:00.940
OK.

01:27:00.940 --> 01:27:07.180
And a deep abiding commitment
to the environment.

01:27:07.180 --> 01:27:11.030
I still-- and know the
results in New England

01:27:11.030 --> 01:27:14.740
and the US of these efforts,
and the huge mountain

01:27:14.740 --> 01:27:20.990
that we have to climb in
this country and New England.

01:27:20.990 --> 01:27:26.120
I've sought, and your
talk speaks to me,

01:27:26.120 --> 01:27:30.080
to something that's much
bigger and more powerful.

01:27:30.080 --> 01:27:35.220
And that is to connect with
people's spiritual belief.

01:27:35.220 --> 01:27:38.780
And having read the
encyclical three times--

01:27:38.780 --> 01:27:39.690
Oh, you have?

01:27:39.690 --> 01:27:44.070
--and he speaks both to
the anger that a lot of us

01:27:44.070 --> 01:27:48.000
feel in environmental
movement, to the hope,

01:27:48.000 --> 01:27:50.490
but also to something you
spoke of in your speech,

01:27:50.490 --> 01:27:52.410
and that is the divine.

01:27:52.410 --> 01:27:57.150
And from me, and I would
love to hear your thoughts,

01:27:57.150 --> 01:27:58.530
how do you--

01:27:58.530 --> 01:28:01.000
has a much bigger
global view than

01:28:01.000 --> 01:28:04.800
I do, rather New
Englanders, how--

01:28:04.800 --> 01:28:06.550
New England is the world.

01:28:06.550 --> 01:28:09.285
How do we as people and--

01:28:12.070 --> 01:28:17.960
get more people like
the pope to proselytize

01:28:17.960 --> 01:28:23.210
about the divinity in
nature, and I think, change

01:28:23.210 --> 01:28:25.180
from within, right?

01:28:25.180 --> 01:28:26.030
The spirit.

01:28:26.030 --> 01:28:28.970
And I think that's part of
what you're speaking to,

01:28:28.970 --> 01:28:30.320
but that to me--

01:28:30.320 --> 01:28:33.010
I know all the
technical solutions.

01:28:33.010 --> 01:28:37.220
I see the actual
practical picture.

01:28:37.220 --> 01:28:40.870
But I think the real movement
is what you're speaking to,

01:28:40.870 --> 01:28:42.502
and that's to connect
with the divine.

01:28:42.502 --> 01:28:43.960
Well, I'm glad you
brought that up,

01:28:43.960 --> 01:28:46.470
because I don't think
I mentioned this.

01:28:46.470 --> 01:28:49.210
Precisely at the time when we
were in Cambodia doing this,

01:28:49.210 --> 01:28:53.380
or maybe a little earlier,
there was an event in Oslo

01:28:53.380 --> 01:28:55.400
that I went to last month.

01:28:55.400 --> 01:28:57.660
They gave me a
Honorary Doctorate.

01:28:57.660 --> 01:29:02.870
But which was a very interesting
event, and the people

01:29:02.870 --> 01:29:04.880
in Cambodia alerted me to it.

01:29:04.880 --> 01:29:09.740
It was an interfaith rain
forest movement event.

01:29:09.740 --> 01:29:11.960
So the pope sent his
representative, direct

01:29:11.960 --> 01:29:13.340
representative.

01:29:13.340 --> 01:29:17.300
People from all-- many
African, Latin American, Asian

01:29:17.300 --> 01:29:20.870
societies, as well as, of
course, Europeans and Americans

01:29:20.870 --> 01:29:21.590
attended that.

01:29:21.590 --> 01:29:26.060
It was a huge event
supported by the rain forest

01:29:26.060 --> 01:29:28.340
initiative in Oslo.

01:29:28.340 --> 01:29:30.650
By the way, Norway is
spending more money

01:29:30.650 --> 01:29:34.450
than any other for
global ecological.

01:29:34.450 --> 01:29:40.190
They also got the most
oil, so there is--

01:29:40.190 --> 01:29:42.690
but they're also into
renewable energy.

01:29:42.690 --> 01:29:46.650
They are spending
it at least too.

01:29:46.650 --> 01:29:48.790
And this was a very
important event,

01:29:48.790 --> 01:29:52.940
because the statement of it
says that rain forests are

01:29:52.940 --> 01:29:56.530
the principle carbon
sinks in the world.

01:29:56.530 --> 01:30:00.730
And the indigenous people
who inhabit those areas

01:30:00.730 --> 01:30:03.310
are the ones who
are suffering most.

01:30:03.310 --> 01:30:07.510
And it is the duty of the world,
the religions of the world,

01:30:07.510 --> 01:30:09.670
to protect those areas.

01:30:09.670 --> 01:30:13.150
And it even mentions
who are the ones who

01:30:13.150 --> 01:30:14.830
are devastating it, right?

01:30:14.830 --> 01:30:18.360
Not personally, but industries.

01:30:18.360 --> 01:30:20.690
So I thought it was-- and
the pope had a very important

01:30:20.690 --> 01:30:22.100
representative.

01:30:22.100 --> 01:30:24.470
The Dalai Lama sent his.

01:30:24.470 --> 01:30:27.710
There were many Chinese
groups, Buddhist groups.

01:30:27.710 --> 01:30:29.030
There were many Hindu groups.

01:30:29.030 --> 01:30:32.370
There were many
Muslim groups as well.

01:30:32.370 --> 01:30:36.830
So if you're interested,
I can send you the link.

01:30:36.830 --> 01:30:39.920
There's a huge sort
of reports on it.

01:30:39.920 --> 01:30:43.250
And they are now going ahead.

01:30:43.250 --> 01:30:46.040
I don't know their program of
action, but it's been set up.

01:30:46.040 --> 01:30:47.150
And it's a recognition.

01:30:47.150 --> 01:30:51.980
Again, like COP 21, it's
a kind of a landmark,

01:30:51.980 --> 01:30:55.910
I think, in many ways
for this kind of change.

01:30:55.910 --> 01:31:01.160
It's a spiritual
attention to it.

01:31:01.160 --> 01:31:02.860
Let's see what happens.

01:31:02.860 --> 01:31:06.400
There are always many
good developments

01:31:06.400 --> 01:31:10.290
that we can feel
optimistic about.

01:31:10.290 --> 01:31:13.610
We'd like to come up here, and
we'll begin with a young woman

01:31:13.610 --> 01:31:18.180
and then, given time,
we'll move down the line.

01:31:18.180 --> 01:31:18.690
Thank you.

01:31:18.690 --> 01:31:22.329
Thank you for your
wonderful talk.

01:31:22.329 --> 01:31:23.370
Please tell us your name.

01:31:23.370 --> 01:31:24.330
Oh, sorry.

01:31:24.330 --> 01:31:27.450
So I'm [INAUDIBLE]
from Boston University.

01:31:27.450 --> 01:31:28.900
I'm from China.

01:31:28.900 --> 01:31:32.310
So it's interesting to
see that you connect

01:31:32.310 --> 01:31:35.790
these ecological thinking
or movement to Taoism

01:31:35.790 --> 01:31:38.070
or Confucianism.

01:31:38.070 --> 01:31:41.080
But it's a little
bit awkward for me

01:31:41.080 --> 01:31:45.900
to say that this is not
ecological thinking.

01:31:45.900 --> 01:31:49.260
It's kind of
spiritual or religion,

01:31:49.260 --> 01:31:52.530
because China is kind of
secular society, right?

01:31:52.530 --> 01:31:55.830
Because of communism.

01:31:55.830 --> 01:31:57.910
So I grew up in China.

01:31:57.910 --> 01:32:00.570
So it took me some time
to understand what is

01:32:00.570 --> 01:32:02.830
religion when I came to the US.

01:32:02.830 --> 01:32:06.090
And according to my
understanding, so transcendence

01:32:06.090 --> 01:32:11.570
or sacred, right, it's much
about the afterlife, or not

01:32:11.570 --> 01:32:15.960
the world, which is not
this current world, right?

01:32:15.960 --> 01:32:20.040
So, but this ecological
thinking or movement

01:32:20.040 --> 01:32:23.070
concerns very much
about the current world.

01:32:23.070 --> 01:32:27.150
And the thing is that, I
think, I wonder whether we

01:32:27.150 --> 01:32:30.220
can argue things only
the other way around,

01:32:30.220 --> 01:32:31.440
is that instead of the--

01:32:33.990 --> 01:32:35.180
Sacred.

01:32:35.180 --> 01:32:39.020
--one to make this really
the ecological thinking

01:32:39.020 --> 01:32:39.870
as a religion, ?

01:32:39.870 --> 01:32:47.940
Right I wonder it is a
secularly usage of religion

01:32:47.940 --> 01:32:49.650
in our secular life, right?

01:32:49.650 --> 01:32:51.870
That actually makes more
sense for me, instead

01:32:51.870 --> 01:32:57.930
of making it as a
spirituality or religion.

01:32:57.930 --> 01:33:00.500
And it--

01:33:00.500 --> 01:33:01.130
OK.

01:33:01.130 --> 01:33:05.820
So that also bring me about your
interpretation, about the word,

01:33:05.820 --> 01:33:07.100
[INAUDIBLE].

01:33:07.100 --> 01:33:09.530
So, the interpretation
of the word [INAUDIBLE]

01:33:09.530 --> 01:33:12.169
is more as homeland, right?

01:33:12.169 --> 01:33:12.710
Yeah, I know.

01:33:12.710 --> 01:33:15.530
And then so I don't understand
why you translate it

01:33:15.530 --> 01:33:18.600
as sacred land.

01:33:18.600 --> 01:33:19.100
No, no.

01:33:19.100 --> 01:33:21.260
I didn't translate
it as sacred land.

01:33:21.260 --> 01:33:24.770
